28 def check_nb_args(expected_nbr):
29  """
30  Decorator used to check number of arguments before running a function
31  """
32 
33  if isinstance(expected_nbr, int):
34  expected_nbr = [expected_nbr]
35 
36  def decorator(function):
37 
38  def wrapper(*args):
39  nbr_args = len(args) - 1 # Because "self"
40  if nbr_args not in expected_nbr:
41  err = "{} parameters expected but {} given".format(expected_nbr, nbr_args)
42  raise TcpCommandException(err + "\nIn function {}".format(function.__name__))
43  result = function(*args)
44  return result
45 
46  return wrapper
47 
48  return decorator

147  # Command interpreter
148  def interpret_command(self, dict_command_received):
149  rospy.logdebug("Command Interpreter - Dict Received : {}".format(dict_command_received))
150  # Check if command is a dict
151  if not isinstance(dict_command_received, dict):
152  msg = f"Cannot interpret command of incorrect type: {type(dict_command_received)}"
153  return self.generate_dict_failure(message=msg)
154  # Check if the dict is well formed
155  if set(dict_command_received.keys()) != {"command", "param_list"}:
156  msg = "Incorrect command format: " + str(dict_command_received)
157  return self.generate_dict_failure(message=msg)
158  # Check if command exists
159  command_name = dict_command_received["command"].upper()
160  if command_name not in self.__commands_dict:
161  return dict_to_packet((self.generate_dict_failure(message="Unknown command")))
162 
163  # Execute command
164  try:
165  param_list = dict_command_received["param_list"]
166  # noinspection PyArgumentList
167  status, list_ret_param, payload = self.__commands_dict[command_name](*param_list)
168  rospy.logdebug("Command Interpreter - {} - {}".format(status, list_ret_param))
169  except (TcpCommandException, TypeError, NotImplementedError) as e:
170  rospy.logerr(f"Command Interpreter - {e}, dict_command_received: {dict_command_received}", exc_info=True)
171  return dict_to_packet(self.generate_dict_failure(command=command_name, message=str(e)))
172 
173  # Save answer Format parameters
174  new_param_list = []
175  for parameter in list_ret_param:
176  if isinstance(parameter, Enum):
177  new_param_list.append(parameter.name)
178  elif isinstance(parameter, bool):
179  new_param_list.append(str(parameter))
180  else:
181  new_param_list.append(parameter)
182 
183  dict_ret = {
184  "status": status, "command": command_name, "list_ret_param": new_param_list, "payload_size": len(payload)
185  }
186 
187  packet_data = dict_to_packet(dict_ret)
188  rospy.logdebug("Command Interpreter - Packet response size {}\nDict response : {}".format(
189  len(packet_data), dict_ret))
190 
191  return packet_data + payload

194  def __generate_functions_dict(self):
195  """
196  Generate a dict with the format : {command_1 : function_to_call_1, command_2 : function_to_call_2...}
197  WARNING -> function name should have the following format : function_to_call_1 = __command_1.lower()
198  For instance GRASP_WITH_TOOL is associated to "__grasp_with_tool"
199  :return: dict
200  """
201  dict_c = dict()
202  # noinspection PyTypeChecker
203  for command in CommandEnum:
204  try:
205  func_adr = getattr(self, "_{}__{}".format(self.__class__.__name__, command.name.lower()))
206  except AttributeError:
207  func_adr = self.__not_implemented_function
208  dict_c[command.name] = func_adr
209 
210  return dict_c
